<H1>Kitaran Sea Calendar</H1>
<P>
The calendar starts in the <I>actual</I> middle of winter.
</P>
<P>
This world has two moons, like Greyhawk:
</P>
<DL>
<DT>Luna</DT>
<DD>The larger moon, similar to our Earth's revolves around the planet
once every 28 days. This gives the calendar its months.</DD>
<DT>Celene</DT>
<DD>The smaller, silvery moon, similar to the moons of Mars, revolves
around the planet once every 91 days. This gives the calendar its 
festivals.</DD>
</DL>
<P>
This gives the residents of the area 12 full months of 28 days each and
four week-long festivals. <BR>
A week consists of seven days:
</P>
<UL>
<LI>Starday</LI>
<LI>Sunday</LI>
<LI>Moonday</LI>
<LI>Godsday (reserved for worship)</LI>
<LI>Waterday</LI>
<LI>Earthday</LI>
<LI>Freeday (usually reserved for a holiday)</LI>
</UL>
<P>
The four festivals are:
</P>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="winter.html#needfest">Needfest</A>, which celebrates the darkest day.</LI>
<LI><A HREF="spring.html#growfest">Growfest</A>, which celebrates the spring growth.</LI>
<LI><A HREF="summer.html#richfest">Richfest</A>, which celebrates the plentiful season.</LI>
<LI><A HREF="autumn.html#brewfest">Brewfest</A>, which celebrates the harvest.</LI>
</UL>
<P>
The Dozenmonth of the moon is therefore:
</P>
<TABLE>
<TR><TD>Needfest</TD><TD>Growfest</TD><TD>Richfest</TD><TD>Brewfest</TD></TR>
